nodes.title: Read each note to set up your run before pressing (Queue Prompt)

widgets_values:
Step 1: Add Your Video Clip
Start Here: Locate the "Load Video (Upload)" section.
Upload Your Clip: Click on the area labeled "Choose video to upload".
Find the video you want to transform and upload it.
Recommended Length: The best length for processing is between 10 to 15 seconds.

Step 2: Check the Video Aspect Ratio
Aspect Ratio Information:
This workflow is designed for videos with a 9:16 aspect ratio (ideal for Instagram and TikTok).
If your video is not in 9:16, you will need to adjust the Width and Height.
Where to Adjust: In the "Width" and "Height" sections, change the numbers to match your video.

Step 3: Set Up and Process a Preview
Preview Settings:
The workflow is set to render only the first 50 frames to let you preview the outcome before committing to processing the entire video.
How to Preview:
Click Queue Prompt to begin processing the 50-frame preview.
Wait for the preview to finish processing so you can see how the transformation looks.

Step 4: Process the Full Video
Ready to Process the Entire Video?:
If you're happy with the preview, you can now render the entire video.
Change Frame Load Cap: Go to the "Frame Load Cap" option and change the value from 50 to 0.
Why Change It? Setting it to 0 will ensure the entire video is processed.
Finalize and Start Processing:
After changing the settings, click Queue Prompt again to begin processing the full video.

Tips for Beginners:
Follow the Notes: Look for any notes in the interfaceâ€”they will guide you step-by-step.
Don't Worry About Advanced Settings: Most of the time, you don't need to adjust anything beyond what is mentioned here.
Aspect Ratio Importance: Ensure the aspect ratio is correct, otherwise the video may look stretched or cropped.
